	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=175818><span id= >calculo</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>/agree<br><br>It really burns me when someone pretends that they alone have the authority to determine that Verant / SoE is wrong for choosing a particular nuance about the game.&nbsp;&nbsp;Certainly before taking the time to complain either in game verbally or out of game on message boards, one should take the time to consider the various implications of a particular item's stats rather than declare that it is an offront to their obviously superior gaming judgement.  The game is too large and the classes too varied for every item to remain economically desirable for all characters.  In other words, like Trooden pointed out, while you may not care that your toolbox weighs a bit more and costs less, to a monk that simply is not acceptable and he must choose the weight reducing backpack you love so dearly.  And, besides, purchasing a heavier container to save a few plat at a lower level is only a temporary solution for anyone who has their head screwed on properly.<br><br>In my humble opinion, it is much more irritating to see how players abuse the game than how the game was designed.  <br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
